  "text": "Despite significant advancements in surgical techniques during the last decades, only a small proportion of patients (20%-30%) are eligible for surgical resection because of tumor location, multifocality, proximity of tumor to vessels, or inadequate functional hepatic reserve. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In an effort to provide treatment for patients who are not candidates for surgery, novel treatment approaches to control and potentially cure liver submit your manuscript | www.dovepress.com",
